    "what_description": "Calopsis andreaeana is an evergreen perennial plant, native to South Africa, belonging to the family Restionaceae. It has a slender stem, typically reaching 1-2 meters in height, with linear, flat or rounded leaves that are 2-5 millimeters in width and 10-25 centimeters in length. The leaves are often glaucous, with a distinctive, powdery coating, and have a blunt or rounded apex. The plant produces small, greenish-brown, cylindrical spikelets, 10-20 millimeters in length, in terminal or axillary inflorescences, containing 3-5 florets. The florets are dioecious, with male and female flowers produced on separate plants.",
