    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Calopsis andreaeana are its anti-inflammatory effects, which have been attributed to the presence of flavonoids in the plant. The bioactive compounds responsible for its antimicrobial properties include saponins, which are capable of inhibiting the growth of various microorganisms. In addition to its antimicrobial properties, Calopsis andreaeana has also been found to possess antioxidant properties, which are due to the presence of volatile oils that can neutralize free radicals in the body. This plant has been used to treat various health conditions, including its antiviral effects, which are believed to be caused by the action of flavonoids on viral replication. The bioactive compounds in Calopsis andreaeana have also been found to exhibit cytotoxic effects, which can be attributed to the presence of triterpenoids that can inhibit cell growth and induce apoptosis.",
